review_blob: Very dark, black pour. Surprisingly mellow and balanced flavor. Not too sweet or overpowering, yet with notes of chocolate, whisky, and butterscotch.
Unusual beer but very delightful. Strong aroma of chardonnay. Sweet caramel taste, very enjoyable but may be too sweet for some.

Very rich and heavy beer; was surprised that this vintage has such a high ABV. Opened a bottle for a friend who insisted he had never had a good smokey beer. Notes of caramel and chocolate, but most powerfully smokey with some sweetness. One of the best smoked beers Ive ever had. The alcohol content and richness balances what would otherwise be overwhelming smokiness.
beer_name: The Bruery Smoking Wood - Rye Barrel

review_blob: Was lucky to try this during a reserve beer tasting for SF Beer Week. Fantastic yet not overly complex taste, exactly how a balanced quad should taste. Exceptional bold aftertaste that makes it truly special.
